<paragraph id="8B9F36D7F355FFDD9A82FAC4FD2ECD5A" blockId="2.[175,660,1287,1314]" box="[175,660,1287,1314]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349">
<heading id="D0D781BBF355FFDD9A82FAC4FD2ECD5A" box="[175,660,1287,1314]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" reason="3">
Subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D54F355FFDD9B09FACBFD2ECD5A" authority="Simpson, 1945" authorityName="Simpson" authorityYear="1945" box="[292,660,1287,1314]" class="Mammalia" family="Suidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Listriodontinae">
LISTRIODONTINAE 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD9BC2FAC4FD2ECD5A" author="SIMPSON G. G." box="[495,660,1288,1314]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" pagination="1 - 350" refId="ref28767" refString="SIMPSON G. G. 1945. - The principals of classification and a classification of Mammals. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 85: 1 - 350." type="journal article" year="1945">Simpson, 1945</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9F36D7F355FFDD9ABAFA8BFC36C9BA" blockId="2.[151,684,1351,1666]" lastBlockId="2.[714,1248,167,1378]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349">
NOTE ON THE AUTHORSHIP OF 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D54F355FFDD9BC5FA8BFE32CDFA" authority="Van der Made (1996)" authorityName="Van der Made" authorityYear="1996" class="Mammalia" family="Suidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Listriodontinae">
LISTRIODONTINAE 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD9ABAFAABFE32CDFA" author="VAN DER MADE J." box="[151,392,1383,1410]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" pagination="3 - 254" refId="ref28896" refString="VAN DER MADE J. 1996. - Listriodontinae (Suidae, Mammalia), their evolution, systematics and distribution in time and space. Contributions to Tertiary and Quaternary Geology 33: 3 - 254." type="journal article" year="1996">Van der Made (1996)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has proposed that 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD9876FAA4FF5BCDDA" author="GERVAIS P." pageId="2" pageNumber="349" refId="ref27264" refString="GERVAIS P. 1859. - Zoologie et paleontologie francaises. Bertrand, Paris, 2 nd ed., 544 p." type="book" year="1859">Gervais (1859)</bibRefCitation>
and not 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD9B66FA44FE44CDDA" author="SIMPSON G. G." box="[331,510,1416,1442]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" pagination="1 - 350" refId="ref28767" refString="SIMPSON G. G. 1945. - The principals of classification and a classification of Mammals. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 85: 1 - 350." type="journal article" year="1945">Simpson (1945)</bibRefCitation>
was the author of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D54F355FFDD9B79FA64FE40CDBA" authorityName="Van der Made" authorityYear="1996" box="[340,506,1448,1474]" class="Mammalia" family="Suidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Listriodontinae">Listriodontinae</taxonomicName>
on the grounds that the former author referred to a group “tribu de listriodontins”. However, resurrecting long forgotten names or authorship for supra-generic categories of zoological groups is not recommended by the latest edition of the 
<emphasis id="B954EAC5F355FFDD980FF984FDBACEFA" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="349">International Code of Zoological Nomenclature</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD983CF9A4FD1ACEFA" author="ICZN" box="[529,672,1640,1666]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" refId="ref27529" refString="ICZN 1999. - International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th ed., International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, xxix + 306 p." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
). In the introduction (p. XXVIII, paragraph 11) it is clearly explained that “an author will be required (without a ruling by the Commission) not to displace a name which has been used as valid by at least 10 authors in 25 publications during the past 50 years, and encompassing a span of not less than ten years, by an earlier synonym or homonym which has not been used as valid since 1899”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33A655CF355FFDD98E7FE0BFC8DCD1A" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9F36D7F355FFDD98E7FE0BFC8DCD1A" blockId="2.[714,1248,167,1378]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349">
In this case, even though the family name Listriodontidae was erected by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD9E31FE2BFB15CA7A" author="ROGER O." box="[1052,1199,487,514]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" refId="ref28749" refString="ROGER O. 1882. - Verzeichnis der bisher bekannten fossilen Saugetiere. Regensburg, 162 p." type="book" year="1882">Roger (1882)</bibRefCitation>
and later by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD990AFDC4FC5ECA5A" author="LYDEKKER R." box="[807,996,520,546]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" pagination="35 - 104" refId="ref27894" refString="LYDEKKER R. 1884. - Indian Tertiary and post- Tertiary Vertebrata. Siwalik and Narbada Bunodont Suina. Memoirs of the Geological Survey of India, Palaeontologica Indica (10) 3 (2): 35 - 104." type="journal article" year="1884">Lydekker (1884)</bibRefCitation>
, according to the new provisions of the 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD99BDFDE4FB90CA3A" author="ICZN" box="[912,1066,552,578]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" refId="ref27529" refString="ICZN 1999. - International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th ed., International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, xxix + 306 p." type="book" year="1999">ICZN (1999)</bibRefCitation>
this should not be taken to mean that the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D54F355FFDD98E7FDA4FCC7CAFA" authorityName="Van der Made" authorityYear="1996" box="[714,893,616,642]" class="Mammalia" family="Suidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Listriodontinae">Listriodontinae</taxonomicName>
was erected by these authors, their publications appearing prior to the end of 1899. To my knowledge there have been only two papers published during the past 50 years which credit the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D54F355FFDD9E20FD24FB05CB7A" authorityName="Van der Made" authorityYear="1996" box="[1037,1215,744,770]" class="Mammalia" family="Suidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Listriodontinae">Listriodontinae</taxonomicName>
to authors other than 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD99B6FCC4FBF1CB5A" author="SIMPSON G. G." box="[923,1099,776,802]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" pagination="1 - 350" refId="ref28767" refString="SIMPSON G. G. 1945. - The principals of classification and a classification of Mammals. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 85: 1 - 350." type="journal article" year="1945">Simpson (1945)</bibRefCitation>
and these are 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD98E7FCEBFC4CCB3A" author="MCKENNA M. C. &amp; BELL S. K." box="[714,1014,807,834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" refId="ref27935" refString="MCKENNA M. C. &amp; BELL S. K. 1997. - Classification of Mammals above the Species Level. Columbia University Press, New York, 631 p." type="book" year="1997">McKenna &amp; Bell (1997)</bibRefCitation>
who give credit to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD98E7FC84FC3BCB1A" author="LYDEKKER R." box="[714,897,840,866]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" pagination="35 - 104" refId="ref27894" refString="LYDEKKER R. 1884. - Indian Tertiary and post- Tertiary Vertebrata. Siwalik and Narbada Bunodont Suina. Memoirs of the Geological Survey of India, Palaeontologica Indica (10) 3 (2): 35 - 104." type="journal article" year="1884">Lydekker (1884)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD9994FC8BFB12CB1A" author="VAN DER MADE J." box="[953,1192,839,866]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" pagination="3 - 254" refId="ref28896" refString="VAN DER MADE J. 1996. - Listriodontinae (Suidae, Mammalia), their evolution, systematics and distribution in time and space. Contributions to Tertiary and Quaternary Geology 33: 3 - 254." type="journal article" year="1996">
<collectingRegion id="49E4F835F355FFDD9994FC8BFC5CCB19" box="[953,998,839,865]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="2" pageNumber="349">Van</collectingRegion>
der Made (1996)
</bibRefCitation>
who gives it to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD9914FCA4FC64CBFA" author="GERVAIS P." box="[825,990,872,898]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" refId="ref27264" refString="GERVAIS P. 1859. - Zoologie et paleontologie francaises. Bertrand, Paris, 2 nd ed., 544 p." type="book" year="1859">Gervais (1859)</bibRefCitation>
. Furthermore, there are no papers published during the 20 
<superScript id="7C559B9FF355FFDD9E6FFC4FFBE9CBEE" attach="left" box="[1090,1107,899,918]" fontSize="8" pageId="2" pageNumber="349">th</superScript>
century that attribute the subfamily name to any of these authors, but there are many that credit Simpson with creating it. For these reasons, we adhere to the latest version of the ICZN and continue to credit 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD9939FBE4FC75CC3A" author="SIMPSON G. G." box="[788,975,1064,1090]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" pagination="1 - 350" refId="ref28767" refString="SIMPSON G. G. 1945. - The principals of classification and a classification of Mammals. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 85: 1 - 350." type="journal article" year="1945">Simpson (1945)</bibRefCitation>
, with the authorship of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D54F355FFDD995BFB84FB8BCC1A" authorityName="Van der Made" authorityYear="1996" box="[886,1073,1096,1122]" class="Mammalia" family="Suidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Listriodontinae">Listriodontinae</taxonomicName>
. This decision accepts the wish of the ICZN “to act in the interests of preserving established usage”. Otherwise, I could easily suggest that the subfamily be credit- ed to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD993DFB0BFC0ACC9A" author="ROGER O." box="[784,944,1223,1250]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" refId="ref28749" refString="ROGER O. 1882. - Verzeichnis der bisher bekannten fossilen Saugetiere. Regensburg, 162 p." type="book" year="1882">Roger (1882)</bibRefCitation>
who published the name Listriodontidae two years before 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD9E40FB24FCA2CD5A" author="LYDEKKER R." pageId="2" pageNumber="349" pagination="35 - 104" refId="ref27894" refString="LYDEKKER R. 1884. - Indian Tertiary and post- Tertiary Vertebrata. Siwalik and Narbada Bunodont Suina. Memoirs of the Geological Survey of India, Palaeontologica Indica (10) 3 (2): 35 - 104." type="journal article" year="1884">Lydekker (1884)</bibRefCitation>
did, thereby nullifying the decision of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B26F355FFDD98E7FAEBFC58CD3A" author="MCKENNA M. C. &amp; BELL S. K." box="[714,994,1319,1346]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349" refId="ref27935" refString="MCKENNA M. C. &amp; BELL S. K. 1997. - Classification of Mammals above the Species Level. Columbia University Press, New York, 631 p." type="book" year="1997">McKenna &amp; Bell (1997)</bibRefCitation>
to credit the name to Lydekker.
</paragraph>
